Some of the posters in this thread (Graal, Walkabout, Castiran and a few others) mention that the Min damage and Max damage seems to be wrong just like I did 3 months ago.<br>
<br>
Correct formula for Min would be: int(DMG/10 +0.5) + bonus<br>
<br>
Max hits is what is causing the most confusion. Your damage table puts a limit to your damage, but this is only visible if you have really high ATK, so while this is obvious to anyone with a primal weapon its not noticeable at all for others.<br>
<br>
The &quot;roof&quot; in the damage table seems to be around 5.7-5.9 depending on class where class is lvl 55 monk, lvl 60 monk and everyone else. There might be an exception for bards with the insane ATK they can get through stacking bugs.<br>
<br>
But let me ask you something. Why do you want a formula for Max hits? You dont have a formula for how to set the Min, MN, Max ratios anyway. Even if you had the TRUE formula for max damge, given to you by god, it wouldnt help you in the slightest if you dont know how to set the Min, MN and Max ratios.<br>
<br>
I am guessing here, but I think you parse your damage to find out which ratios work for you. If you dont parse this then this damage calculator is worthless, because you are just guessing.<br>
<br>
But if you do parse it, then you dont need the formula for max damage. Sure it wont hurt, but it wont help either. Its just added weight in the formula and it makes the formula more cumbersome to use.<br>
<br>
My first reply in this thread was a joke of course. I am not suggesting that you use cha and int or some other nonsense.<br>
But the point is that it would work just as good. Sure you might have to use another Min, MN, Max ratio but users are encouraged (by Luthair) to change those settings to fit your needs anyway.<br>
